8 An Act relating to motor vehicles; amending 47 O.S.
2021, Section 585, which relates to denial,
9 suspension or revocation of license; modifying
maximum amount of certain administrative fine;
10 amending 74 O.S. 2021, Section 3601.1, as last
amended by Section 36, Chapter 29, O.S.L. 2023 (74
11 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 3601.1), which relates to
maximum number of full-time-equivalent employees;
12 modifying maximum number of full-time-equivalent
employees for certain agencies; and providing an
13 effective date.
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 585, is
17 amended to read as follows:
18 Section 585. A. The Commission may deny any application for
19 license, or suspend or revoke a license issued, or impose a fine, in
20 accordance with the provisions of the Administrative Procedures Act,
21 Section 250 et seq. of Title 75 of the Oklahoma Statutes. If the
22 applicant or licensee is a used motor vehicle salesperson, the
23 Commission shall in like manner also notify the person, firm,
24 association, corporation or trust with whom associated, or in whose
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2997 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 asso ciation the applicant or licensee is about to enter. The
2 Commission shall have the power to compel the production of records
3 and papers bearing upon the complaints. The Commission shall have
4 the power to subpoena and bring before it any person in this state,
5 or take testimony of any such person by deposition, with the same
6 fees and mileage and in the same manner as prescribed by law in
7 judicial procedure before courts of the state in civil cases. Any
8 party to the hearing shall have the right to the attendance of
9 witnesses in his behalf upon designating to the Commission the
10 person or persons sought to be subpoenaed. If the Commission shall
11 determine that any licensee is guilty of violation of any of the
12 provisions of this act, the license of the licensee shall be
13 suspended or revoked, or a fine imposed as authorized by this act.
14 B. The Commission may assess a fine not to exceed One Hundred
15 Dollars ($100.00) against a used motor vehicle dealer who:
16 1. Willfully fails to deliver certificates of title to
17 purchasers of used motor vehicles within thirty (30) days of the
18 sale of the vehicles;
19 2. Fails to properly reassign the certificate of title to a
20 used motor vehicle as required by law upon the sale or transfer of
21 ownership of the used motor vehicle;
22 3. Sells an extended insurance warranty to a purchaser, but
23 fails to provide a copy of the warranty to the purchaser or fails to
24 disclose who the third party insurer will be; or
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB2997 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 4. Delivers a used motor vehicle to a potential purchaser with
2 the intent to sell the vehicle, but does not complete the
3 transaction within fifteen (15) calendar days of the delivery of the
4 used motor vehicle.
5 C. An appeal from the decision of the Commission to suspend or
6 revoke a license or to impose a fine shall be taken in accordance
7 with Article II of the Administrative Procedures Act, Section 308a
8 et seq. of Title 75 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
9 D. Any applicant or licensee who knowingly or willfully makes
10 or causes to be made any false statement of a fact required under
11 the provisions of Section 581 et seq. of this title shall be subject
12 to an administrative fine not to exceed One Ten Thousand Dollars
13 ($1,000.00) ($10,000.00).
14 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 74 O.S. 2021, Section 3601.1, as
15 last amended by Section 36, Chapter 29, O.S.L. 2023 (74 O.S. Supp.
16 2025, Section 3601.1), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 3601.1. A. For purposes of Sections 3601.1 through
18 3603 of this title, the term "employee" means a full-time employee
19 or any number of part-time employees whose combined weekly hours of
20 employment equal those of a full-time employee, but shall not
21 include temporary employees working on a seasonal basis between May
22 1 and October 31.
23 B. Beginning July 1, 2008, the maximum number of full-time-
24 equivalent employees for each of the following agencies, boards,
